reviews:
The bed is sooo comfy! They surprised my husband with sweets and a banner, as the trip to Roland Garros was a gift for his 30th birthday.
We loved our stay and would come back any time. The hotel is near the Arc de Triomphe and everything important is in near distance. The breakfast is delicious.

This hotel is 'hidden' behind the lovely Arc the Triomphe - the location is very central.
I travel a lot to Paris, and it's a lot of fun but very exhausting too. Having a good sleep is very important, and I give them a 10+ for letting me sleep like a baby. The mattress is fantastic, the rooms are beautiful, and they serve a healthy breakfast! All ingredients for getting the most out of Paris.

Just touched down in the enchanting city of Paris, fresh from our delightful Corsican adventure. We flew into Orly Airport and let me tell you, entrusting our hotel to arrange transportation was an absolute game-changer! Our seamless journey to the hotel was worth every penny.

As for our home away from home, we've found a delightful hideaway in the Hidden Hotel. The comfort of the beds is beyond compare and the staff are the epitome of hospitality. If you're considering a stay, I wholeheartedly recommend opting for their breakfast – it's a culinary delight and a brilliant start to your Parisian day. 👍🏼🥐🗼

When I walked into the room I thought this has gotta be a mistake? It was so small and cramped I was instantly disappointed. I should have checked the size. The shower had a sprinkle coming out and zero pressure so it took 15 minutes to wash yourself. The toilet had 1 roll of toilet paper and was so small I struggled to sit down on the loo without bumping into everything. And everything can be heard under the massive gap in the door with zero ventilation so be warned. I've travelled all over the world and this is the smallest and worst 4 star room I've ever stayed in. The bar was closed by midnight and the mouse running across the floor all night was the only amusement. The morning breakfast was average but having lived in France for 2 years I expected better. A poor selection of fruits, coffees, Teas and hot food to eat. The staff however were all very young (18-23) and very friendly but it appeared like they were all amateurs helping each other out. I'm not a moaner and I've never written a review before but I wish I'd have read this before booking. I would have stayed elsewhere and payed more. Zero room with a zero view and although the staff were nice it doesn't cut the mustard for me. and they still have not refunded me my deposit. If you are looking for a romantic weekend then stay elsewhere even if it costs more.

This is my third stay at the Hidden Hotel and they continue to exceed my expectations. I had a different room every time and they are all spacious and cozy. The bathroom is equipped with all amenities a traveler needs and then some. The breakfast is fantastic and they will make fresh pancakes or omelettes just for you. Staff is attentive and courteous. Location ist wonderful. I will definitely be back.

We loved the hotel, the location, the room, the breakfast and for sure the level of service by a group of young and enthousiastic staff during our stay. What we experienced was a great rest in the hotel.

A really nice and cozy little hotel in a very good spot near Arc de Triomphe. Our room was clean and interieur was comfortable and thoughtful. The staff was extremely friendly. We also enjoyed the great breakfast buffet. Would definitely recommend it.

This is an amazing hotel with great staff and great service. Beds are extremely comfortable and if you need anything - just ask! The location couldn’t be any better. Great restaurants in the area. Very safe. I highly recommend staying at the Hidden Hotel.

Hidden hotel Paris is genuinely one of the best hotels in the city. The staff is very friendly and helpful and offer excellent service. The hotel rooms are very nice and furnished with amazing beds from coco mat. Lastly does the hotel offer an amazing location on Rue de l'Arc de Triomphe. This means that it’s close to a lot of important sights, restaurants and places to shop at.

Loved the Hidden, the best hotel in Paris, rooms clean, the staff was really friendly and helpful. Breakfast was really great and last but not least they have the best of the best beds ever!!! COCO-MAT beds. Overall we loved everything!! Thank you Hidden for the great stay in your beautiful hotel!!!

We had a great stay at the Hidden Hotel.
Our room as well as the main lobby were a very cosy place, friendly and nice personell. Also greatly located at a calm street but a 10 min walk from the Arc the Triumph.

We got this recommended by friends and we were so pleased we followed up on their recommendation as this was the perfect hotel for us. The staff were all friendly and were always there to help. The rooms were comfortable and quiet and a really convenient location right with lots of shops close by.

Perfect location and perfect staff. I wish they had more room service options but overall great and compare to other hotels in Paris; pretty modernized.
I would definitely book this hotel if I ever plan to go back to Paris again.

Good: friendly, helpful staff, breakfast was great, rooms were cleaned and had welcome snacks and chocolate. It was basically as good as the Ritz Carlton I’ve stayed in. It had many facilities in the room and I’m very grateful.

OK: Paid for breakfast but the sausages ran out, and the staff said they’ll not make another batch at 10am (My girlfriend was grumpy towards me the whole day). But overall, the experience was positive. I was traveling with a more senior person as well, I think I would picked a hotel a bit closer to the metro station, the walk was about 6 mins but it’s not much of a problem for young people.

Best hospitality without a doubt. Personnel was incredibly helpful and kind. Immaculate vibes with aesthetically pleasing design and interior. The bed was like sleeping in heaven. 11/10 would recommend

Small room but had everything I needed. Excellent hospitality. Sustainability is infused throughout. Love the place. Will definitely return.
Comfortable bed. Room service at 06:00 spot on. Great insider tips. They also have their own application.

Very nice hotel with a beauty room on a perfect location. The staff was very friendly. The hotel is 5 minutes walk from the champs a lychee. I would definitely recommend this to my friends and family.

I really enjoyed my stay here. It felt like a home away from home for 6 days. The staff was wonderful and highly professional in all interactions. The modern decor of the hotel and my room was inviting, comfortable and beautiful. It is conveniently located near plenty of restaurants, shops, and the Arc de Triomphe. I would highly recommend a stay here and I am looking forward to returning.

Had a wonderful stay at Hidden Hotel. Everything was about just perfect, services, rooms, atmosphere and vibe. Most importantly location was great. Near to most of the sightseeings and different services.

This hotel was very special, we loved the stylish decor, the fabulous breakfast and the chocolate brownies were to die for! But the most exceptional part of our stay was the helpfulness and friendliness of the staff, nothing was too much trouble and always with a smile. We felt very welcome and would definitely come back. Thank you.

Everything about the Hidden Hotel was wonderful. The staff are so friendly and make you feel extremely welcome the minute you walk in the door. Our room was immaculately appointed and the decor of the room and indeed the entire hotel is perfect. Probably the most comfortable hotel bed I have ever slept in. Breakfast was lovely and so nice to see different offerings, all served in the extremely tasteful dining/bar area. They location was excellent, just a few minutes from the Arc de Triomphe and the Champs Elysées. I cannot recommend this hotel highly enough. We're sorry we only had one night here and would not hesitate to book again for a longer stay. Thank you all.

The best bed I ever laid down on!!! Staff was amazing and helpful as well! Everything was very well prepared and comfortable I’m grateful to have stayed there and wish I could have stayed more. Definitely will come back.

Very nice hotel ideally situated only 5 min from Arc de Triomphe…Outstanding breakfast with a lot of choice…nice and relaxed ambiance at the bar in the evening, good cocktails mixed with dedication and love… also small things to eat very friendly staff

We rate The Hidden Hotel a 5++++++. Everything about the hotel is absolutely top notch: the location, rooms, breakfast, vibe, and especially the staff. Everyone was helpful, friendly, and accommodating. WE LOVED THE HIDDEN HOTEL! We will definitely be back!

The hotel is adorable, the rooms have everything you need, the location is fantastic, super close to more than one metro station, walking distance to the Arch of Triumph, their breakfasts are delicious but the best of all is the people that work there, they are always ready to help with anything you might need and you can see that they love what they do, their general manager is wonderful, she really has created a home away from home experience. We cannot wait to back!

We stayed for two nights at Hidden to celebrate a birthday. We had a very warm welcome and a very cute and sweet surprise on arrival in our room. Also, they made a delicieus moelleux aux chocolat at breakfast with a candle and a 'Happy birthday' flag, really kind and extremely appreciated.
The location is perfect and the bed feels like you're sleeping on clouds, heavenly ;-)
We enjoyed every minute of our stay at Hidden, hightly recommended!

Very clean and quaint hotel. Very helpful and lovely staff with a great breakfast. Check in was easy and the rooms weren’t very large but what it lacked in size, it more than made up for in comfort and charm. Will definitely visit again anytime we go Paris
Excellent hotel. The location could not possibly be better. Walking distance to everything including the Metro and yet on a quiet street. The staff is extremely helpful, friendly and multilingual.

This hotel is highly recommendable. The interior is cozy and nicely decorated. Our sensation room was spacious and comfortable. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Very good breakfast. It’s located nearby metro stations and underground parkings.

Lovely and charming small boutique hotel, very well situated and easily accessible by public transport. Steps from the Arc de Triomphe. Everything is tiny but very well thought of! Amazing breakfast buffet and lovely bar. Staff is very friendly.

Front desk was very friendly and tried to accommodate as much as possible as it was my first time in Paris. I was at the top of the list for early check-in (last minute request on my part); my room was available at 1. Breakfast was tasty. Room service took a long time the first time but food was fresh and presented beautifully. Hotel is small overall but cozy and located near lots of stores, restaurants, and the arch. I would recommend for couples!

A great hotel with perfect location within walkable distance of both the Arc de Triomphe and Champs Elysees. Hotel is very nicely furnished and the staff were extremely welcoming. Bed was one of the comfiest I have ever slept in! Would def reocmmend

The hotel is in the best location and the hospitality and service was top. Very relaxing, great breakfast, very nice rooms, will stay again next time in Paris. Staff is very friendly and the rooms comfortable.

Absolutely Amazing, the hotel has amazing decor and is relaxing, the rooms are luxurious, spacious and perfect. The hotel is in the best location and the hospitality and service was top quality. I can’t fault this place and would recommend to anyone.

Brilliant Staff, hotel and location!
Feels like a home away from home.
Very pleasant and eco friendly hotel.
Definitely recommend it when in Paris!
Rooms are nice and cozy and spacious.
Can’t wait to visit again.

We stayed at the Hidden Hotel for my husband’s birthday weekend.

The staff were very responsive and helpful leading up to the trip. They assisted me with surprising my husband and a last minute dinner reservation.

The hotel itself is beautifully decorated and lives up to its environmentally friendly name. Hotel slippers and robes are provided. The shower is ah-mazing and the room is beautifully equipped. Breakfast comprised of a delicious spread of pastries, fruits and drinks.

The hotel is located perfectly for anyone looking to explore the main attractions in Zone 1 of Paris. It has easy access to the metro and public transport for exploring different parts of the staff.

The staff are wonderful, friendly and welcoming. Thank you Julian, Thomas and Rebecca for all your assistance.

Would absolutely recommend.

This is such a fabulous hotel in every sense. Great location and also great that it is in a quite 'hidden' location.

The beds and pillows will guarantee a perfect nights sleep, follow that with the most delicious breakfast.

And kudos to all the lovely staff. Only hotel where I have stayed were ALL the staff are naturally super friendly and helpful

Super cool hotel: great location; clean and well equipped; really comfortable bed; and with excellent staff!
This is ideal if you need or want to be pretty central but don’t want the big chain experience.

Interesting and very individual beautiful rooms.
Amazing comprehensive breakfast and adorable people everywhere in this hotel.
Taking into consideration that it was a business trip; I enjoyed my stay in Hidden Hotel very much.

The Check-in process was very smooth. Their breakfast is amazing and healthy. The staff is nice and courteous. The hotel is very clean and located max 15 minutes from all the places you'd like to see!!

Wonderful atmosphere, service minded staff, clean rooms and calm surroundings and one can open the windows. And beds are fantastic. I always sleep like a baby. Thank you for a pleasant and wonderful stay Alinde and see you soon again

The hotel was amazing, perfect for a long weekend away. Great location, clean sheets and rooms, staff were very friendly and food was amazing. Would highly recommend to anyone wanting a lovely romantic trip away.

Absolutely sensational. Gorgeous design, fantastic service, amazing products!
Perfect location, so close to everything that you want to see and in a lovely neighbourhood.
Highly highly recommended.
Thank you so much!

Really disappointed with this hotel , beautiful from
the outside & reception area. Rooms are advertised has Soundproof they are not , could hear people walking around with their shoes & going to toilet.

I asked for a quiet room , not slept well because of this .
The shower is awful & cheap difficult to get the temperature right without the smaller shower turning on . And not clean .

Won’t be staying again

Excellent location (to many Metro lines) and good value for the money. Would definitely go back. The only drawback was that we had a street-facing view, so it was fairly noisy. Staff was terrific--helping us make reservations and recommending their favorite places, and never made us feel like dumb Americans.

Very nice rooms, well designed, just big enough. Good shower. Very nice service at reception / breakfast and bar. Excellent location nearby Arc de Triomphe. Wifi worked well and a complimentary bottle of water in the room. Worth another visit.

Great hotel with nice clean rooms and good service. The location is 10/10 and offers as a great base for city exploration by foot or subway. The breakfast is fresh and nice with good coffee.

The rooms are bit on the small size and it can be a little noisy at night due to ventilation in the windows that cannot be closed. Also the ventilation in the toilet and shower cannot be turned off and can be annoying.

All in all it’s a great hotel in Paris that is worth every cent you pay and we will definitely come back when we’re visiting Paris!

Came here for our honeymoon. Outstanding service, friendly attitude and great breakfast buffet.
The friendly concierges were extremely helpful, the atmosphere in the bar/entry area was exquisite and the rooms were stunning.
Location-wise, it was 2 minutes walk from Champs'elysee, the arc d'triumph and several metro-lines which made getting around the entirety of paris really easy.

I love this hôtel with all my heart! The people especially. This is home for me twice a year. Breakfast is always good and fresh before attacking the city with my camera!
Je vous aimes! Merci avec amour

Xavier

From the welcoming at reception. we arrived at 01:00 in the morning and everything was done smoothly. The rooms are clean as can be. the breakfast was amazing and the staff, what wonderfull people!!
The location couldnt be better, a 5 minute walk from the Metro. With lovely resturaunts and bars around the hotel. I would come back for SURE!

This hotel is just wonderful. We recently stayed here and booked 3 rooms, including the suite. It's not only a nice hotel to look at, its so close to everything. We walked almost everywhere and if we needed, the train station was close. The shower was nice and hot. The bed was just right. There was a small hiccup with the transportation to the airport but the wonderful ladies at the front desk got it sorted out and we made it with more than enough time. I'm so thankful that the Youtube channel Les Frenchies made a video on this hotel.

One of the quietest and best sleeping hotels I’ve ever stayed. The staff were all super friendly and accommodating as well. Would highly recommend Hidden Hotel to anyone travel to Paris. The hotel is close to the metro, Arc and entertainment.

Overall nice stay, we stayed in sensation room.

Pros:
Breakfast, location, staff, cleanliness, and service

Cons:
Bed comfort, size of toilet room (very tight), and shower ventilation.

We would recommend this hotel, would recommend upgrading to a larger room, unfortunately it was not available when we booked.

We stayed at this fabulous hotel as a group of 17 coming to celebrate a special birthday. Firstly, the staff cannot do enough and are super friendly and helpful. The rooms are small but the beds are really comfy and equipped with everything you need with modern decor. The breakfast is well stocked with all the choice you would expect with great coffee. The hotel is located in a great location close to really cool bars and restaurants and 5 mins walk to the arc de Triomphe and metro. We will be coming back to this hotel as it is a great discovery! Thank you all again for accommodating such a large group. 😀

Excellent hotel with wonderful staff who really made us so welcome and could not be more attentive. Beds are super comfortable, sustainable touches everywhere and breakfast is delicious.
We were there with a group of friends and everyone loved their stay. Special mention to Alice, Julian and Suzannah who were always there for us but every member of staff were wonderful. Thank you to The Hidden Family. 😊

Yes the rooms are on the small side but then what do you expect when you're so centrally located! What made this stay were the staff. Each and every one of them were happy, attentive and made our stay better than we could ever have hoped for. Special mentions to Suzannah, Alice & Julian but then again, all the staff were a credit to the hotel.

The personal touch, the spotless venue, the chic detail, the sustainability policy - everything about this hotel is fantastic. The staff are all warm and friendly and cannot do enough to help you. The food is all prepared fresh and the choice is outstanding. The bed was the most comfortable I have ever slept in too!
I travel overseas all the time with work and this is definitely one I will be returning to on a personal level

Excellent Hotel, Staff, Location, Food, Simply everything was excellent.
It's located in the best area and it is truly a HIDDEN GEM in the middle of everything.
Staff are simply the nicest you'd meet and the food is great as well.

I specifically chose the Hidden Hotel after some research because I wanted to make sure that I'd have a nice stay in a clean and modern environment. The rooms and public areas stick to a minimalist design in earth tones with stone and wood accents - it creates a relaxing and cozy atmosphere. I also really enjoyed the drapes around our bed and was surprised by how comfortable the coconut fibre mattress was. The staff was friendly and attentive and the breakfast buffet was delicious (you can even ask for fresh pancakes which are then served at your table).

It is reasonably priced for what you get and I want to stress again how friendly and helpful everybody was. I will definitely be back for my next stay in Paris!

We had a fantastic stay here. Friendly staff, amazing service, wonderful room, delicious breakfast and welcoming approach. Thank you for making our stay so special. Location is perfect - walking distance from Arc of Triumph X Lots of small restaurants around with reasonable prices and excellent food choice x

The best hotel in Paris!!! Excellent location, staff and overall fabulous . Thank you 🖤🖤I wouls stay here again and bring family and fruends.Its surrounded by girgeous french bistros and bars anda few minutes walk to the Arch and lots of wonderful shops.

Most romantic, cute, quaint place to stay in Paris. If you come across this hotel don’t hesitate, book it. Customer service is A++, they have a cute little bar, everybody is super nice and friendly. I did not speak very good French but everyone who works here speaks English with a very cute accent :) I got the room with the terrace and it was so worth it. I will definitely come back here and I don’t think I will stay anywhere else when I am in Paris. Thank you Hidden Hotel for showing me an awesome time.

Amazing stay, spacious room with comfortable bed and amenities, friendly staff, delicious breakfast options, reasonably priced. Conveniently located close to Arc de Triomphe and Champs Elysees. Would definitely return!

Staff was very welcoming and awesome.They assisted in all needs. Received a hearty welcome along with a tour. The rooms look and were kept as clean as the photos. I look forward to staying again. I believe I was in the Intuition room which was comfortable. This Place made my stay exceptional.

We had an amazing stay. The Hidden hotel is such a great place to stay in Paris. Well located, it is warm and welcoming. The hotel is iconic, the design and the style of the room is marvellously unique. The team at the hotel was all about meeting the guest’s expectations and needs. We definitely will come back again

My partner and I stayed at this hotel for a city break in Paris and it was the most perfect stay. The staff were very helpful and kind, particularly Rebecca and Alinda. Our room was cozy, the right temperature and the bed was very comfortable! Breakfast was fresh, with a nice variety of choices and nothing was too much to ask. Not to mention this hotel is perfectly situated, a few minutes from the Arc de Triomphe and a 20 minute walk from the Eiffel Tower. Will certainly be returning!

Top notch hotel in excellent location minutes walk from Arc de Triumph. Stayed here our first night in Paris and staff could not have been more friendly or accommodating. There was an initial misunderstanding regarding the rooms, and Rebecca at the front desk went above and beyond to make it right and our stay enjoyable. Rooms are tastefully decorated and the higher end rooms are quite spacious. Highly recommend staying.

We loved our stay for 7 nights. The hotel is clean and quiet and beautiful. Decor is minimalist and clean. Beds are super comfortable, pillows are perfect and the bathroom water runs hot and perfect. Excellent bathroom amenities. The staff here are efficient and friendly and super helpful. Cannot fault a thing!

We have the most wonderful stay at the hotel. The staff who were so helpful, polite, cheerful and accommodating. They provided service with the smile and were willing to meet all our requests. The location of the hotel, walking distance from the Arc de Triomphe, Champs Elysee, and Metros could not be beat. The rooms were of a good size, with all amenities, and clean. I would highly recommend getting the breakfast at the hotel which had a wide range of food, with fresh made pancakes, and eggs. Overall an amazing experience. I would recommend this hotel to all.

Such a lovely hotel, we had an amazing time there. The room is very clean and aircon was always on and cold which was super amazing to comeback to after a long day. Staff couldn't be more attentive and super friendly plus breakfast was just spot on. This hotel suits couples especially as the shower/bath tub in the middle of the room and not separate

Such a good experience, the team is professional kind and helpful...definitely a real 4 stars in Paris.
The rooms are clean, the location is the most accessible.
I have also test the service in the bar which was very nice with a real barmaid...

Hidden Hotel may be small, but their service is mighty! They were able to help us with ordinary, difficult and off-hours requests, always without a problem. The breakfast spread, and serving staff, always making sure we had what we needed and making omlettes or pancakes for us. The quiet location (about as quiet as one can expect in an urban setting) and easy walk to Arc de Triomphe and Metro make it a great location. Rental bikes and scooters are literally outside the door. We would not hesitate to go back for our next visit to Paris.

The hotel is tastefully decorated with quality fixtures. While a small hotel, Hidden Hotel has all the services you would need: 24-hour front desk, room service, restaurant on site... Staff was very responsive to our email questions before we arrived. I would definitely come back!

Wonderful stay in this lovely small 'ish', niche hotel in the centre of Paris. The staff, from the owners down, were all excellent, attentive and couldn't have been more helpful. We loved our four days there and will certainly use this hotel again when we visit Paris in the future. A bientot Hidden family.

Hidden Hotel was amazing! Very cool and chic lobby and rooms, very nice and professional staff, very nice amenities in the room (coffee, drinks, candy), great location as well. Very comfortable and welcoming hotel, highly recommend!!

My stay at the Hidden Hotel was a last minute choice but in retrospect, it was an excellent decision to have done so! This intimate hotel is superbly located, the in-room amenities are outstanding, and the staff are extremely accommodating! In particular, breakfast was delicious and the bed was supremely comfortable. Hidden Hotel was the perfect refuge after a long day of sightseeing & shopping in the midst of a Parisian heatwave!

What a hotel. Brilliant location. It is so close to the arc de Triomphe and metro. Also walking distance to the main shopping at champs- elysees and about 30-45 min walk to the Eiffel tower. The staff were so friendly and made the visit to the hotel perfect. Clean and modern rooms and the bed was so comfy! Will be staying here again.

Great area, great team, small but nice rooms. The hotel was very nice. We came during business trip and the hotel's team were taking care of everything we asked.
Wonderful hospitality.
We will come visit again when we'll arrive to Paris.

I haven’t stayed at the hidden hotel before in Paris and I don’t speak French but to say they went above and beyond is an understatement. I couldn’t get a taxi to get me to the office I needed to be at and one of the ladies from reception came out on to the street for over 25 minutes to help me find one due to the train strike, she even offered to help me take the metro if I couldn’t get one.

I could have had a really bad morning however due to her and the lady at breakfast making sure I didn’t leave without my tea I had a much better morning and for that o was so grateful.

To the 2 really nice ladies in the hidden hotel thank you so much for your kindness, small gestures of kindness make a big difference and you did make a difference to my day.

Excellent concierge service for booking and recommending restaurants ! Very Friendly staff who made you feel at home and welcomed with lots of personal touches. A refreshing boutique hotel to escape the busy city - made you forget you were in a big city ! Delicious breakfast! Highly recommend Hidden Hotel Paris!
The room was very comfortable and beautifully decorated.

Everything is very welcoming and everyone is extremely customer ''caring''.
All is accurately organized and other services like taxi and other consultations on round-about is gently presented.
Location is just great within the read of all key routes and communications.

First time back to Paris in 5 years, this time for work with a colleague who recommended Hidden Hotel. Quirky, eco, super friendly and helpful staff, this boutique hotel is perfect for those wanting to enjoy the buzz of Paris then retreat to a immaculately clean, simple space for a deep, undisturbed night's sleep. The coco-mat bed with a selection of pillows, drencher shower with sustainable brand toiletries, fresh white linen and towels make for a space that is both relaxing and refreshing. I slept so well, I didn't make breakfast, but the aroma of warm French patisserie and fresh coffee greeted me in the lobby as I headed out to meetings. My first return to Paris in several years, and the first of many visits to Hidden Hotel, I am sure.

The Hidden Hotel in Paris truly is a hidden gem located close to the Arc De Triomphe, the Champs Elysee and surrounded by a wide range of bars, cafes and restaurants. The Accommodation is beautiful and the staff are all very friendly and helpful, nothing is too much trouble. The Hotel has a cute little bar area with resonantly priced drinks for a pre dinner drink or two. The breakfasts are also superb. I have travelled all around the world and the Hidden Hotel is definitely one of the nicest, friendliest hotels I’ve ever stayed at. I would most certainly recommend a stay here. Thanks again team, we will be back

Nice rooms, very nice mandarin sent in the rooms. Coco-Mat bed is a big plus.
Quit area close to Arc de Triumph and Avenue des Champs-Élysées.
I did not have breakfast this time, but this is my fourth stay at this excellent hotel.
I can really recommend this hotel

So glad we chose to stay at the Hidden Hotel. Decided to pay a bit more for our holiday this year and it was sooo worth it. This place is special and if you want the perfect Paris getaway look no further!!! Incredible breakfast, relaxing atmosphere, friendly staff and lovely bedrooms. It's a great place to come back to after being out and about. We frequently found ourselves coming back for drinks at the bar in the afternoon/evening. (Excellent music choices). Can't praise the Hidden highly enough. They go the extra mile and they have the check-in welcome Down to a T. Would absolutely love to stay again. Also great location (but also quiet as off the main drag).

The Hidden Hotel is unique and amazing. The service is wonderful, the entire staff is very attentive and provide personalized service. The breakfast area is very cozy and the selection is unbelievable. Rooms are modern, clean and all amenities are provided. The location, close to the Arc de Triomphe is unbeatable. This hotel is a true gem.

Very helpful crew,
Wonderful, diverge and healthy breakfast , which includes coffee and omlet at your choice , wonderful salad and fruits, yougurts, pies, croissants and so on ....
Definitely a good choice 😊

Very clean, excellent stuff, super perfect breakfasts, very nice interior. Rooms are small, but very nice and beautiful. Location also is great - 5 minutes till metro and 10 minutes walking distance till Palais des Congress. I will make reservation here again next time:).

Visited hidden hotel as attended EuroPCR conference. The hotel was close enough to the conference centre to walk. Perfectly situated a few minutes from the Arch de Triomphe and Champs-Élysées.
The staff were very welcoming and helpful. Nothing seemed a bother for them.

Will visit again when in Paris,

Thank you all x

Intermediary rates for luxury services.
I had a wonderful 3-day stay at this wonderful little hotel located in a great area.
At last, a hotel with a soul! And the beds are unbelievable...
Many thanks to the staff who were very concerned by my well-being throughout the entire stay.
Strongly recommended!

We had a fantastic stay at the Hidden Hotel! The beds are super comfortable and the room was very clean. We had a room with a terrace, which was great to enjoy a drink after a long day of walking. The breakfast is really nice as well, with lots of options.
The team is very friendly, and we loved the personalized service! We went to Paris to celebrate my mom’s birthday, and the team went out of their way to help celebrate this occasion, amongst other things by decorating our room - such a nice touch!
We will definitely come back.

I loved my stay at the Hidden Hotel. Such a great location with greatly styled rooms and delicious breakfast! Staff were very friendly and helpful. I was really grateful for access to the motorised scooters to zip around on. I will definitely be returning and telling my friends.

good location and the service is great. love all the natural, minimalistic decor. however, the rooms are extremely small, and yes, even by Parisian standards. NOTE- we got an upgraded room, and it's hard not to hit something if you turn the corner, and I'm 5'2 staying with my husband who's 5'9.

Everything was perfect,l from the staff friendliness and helpfulness to cleanness of the room! Location is very convenient, i booked the exception suite and it was very nice and clean! I was really happy that i chose hidden hotel for my stay

Hidden hotel is a beautiful and sustainable hotel in Paris, with lovely Alinde amd her team giving the best service and being great hosts. We are enjoing three nights here, and the rooms are so nice, delicate and comfortable. The breakfast is superb and a must-have. I recommend Hidden Hotel to everyone. Best regards, Marianne (and friend Anja)

We much enjoyed our stay at this hidden gem.
Room was on the small side, but nicely designed and with good furniture (well equiped).
Staff is super friendly.
A little chaotic at breakfast, but worth the wait

Hidden Hotel is one of our favourite places. The room was beautiful and comfortable - the bath tub was a real treat! The room service was prompt and delicious and the breakfast buffet is not to be missed. This was our fourth visit and we will definitely keep choosing Hidden Hotel.

Very nice staff although the room was Tiny the bed was comfortable. Not too much street noise either. Breakfast was great, very enjoyable. The decor is a little odd in trying to be different but it nearly works, is quite pleasant and not too jarring.
Overall I would stay here again.
The area is pleasantly polite - with an awesome Korean BBQ grill restaurant not too far away.

we love it, stay was perfect, all the personnel was lovely, available, friendly. The chief concierge was incredibility friendly, available for any information and flexible to accommodate last minute requests.
We do recommend it.

The hotel is very clean, helpful staff, however the air conditioning system wasn’t working the room was very hot, they tried to fix it twice it didn’t work, they didn’t offer another room.
Breakfast area is very small, not too much variety in the breakfast. Wifi is working fine
